Being entrepreneur is not easy, it can be lonely, frustrated, and even hopeless sometimes, so be prepared for it. After all, success requires persistence, persistence, and persistence.


Do I need to invest once I commit to join as a co-founder?

For the early stage, I have enough resources for the product development, as well as bringing the final product to market. You are welcome to invest any amount you want since you will be the founder of our company. But it is not necessary and is totally up to you.


When can we expect to launch the product?

Generally, we can expect to launch the product to market in about six months as the prototype was built already. Hopefully we can see the positive cash flow within a year. Again, it depends on our development process and how much time and effort we put in. 


Can I be part time as a co-founder?

It will only work for a short period of time if that is necessary for you. Once our development is on track, I believe full time is required. Being laser-focused and hardworking is the only way to make our dream come true. 


What kind of skills do I need to have?

As a tech cofounder, you will focus on technological development, firmware, PCB design, mobile app&server deployment. You don’t have to master every single detail right now, and you should have a vision that your skills will be kept up with our development process to fulfill all tasks coming along.

A little background

Entrepreneurship and Challenge are something I am always looking to embrace for. Right after I graduated from my Ph.D study, I started my own business. Being an entrepreneur is not easy, I spent countless time and energy to work. But it is a truly rewarding journey, and I gained some valuable experience in manufacturing, management, marketing and distribution. The Success of my 1st company has enabled me to have the opportunity to seek my real passion: innovation for home. With the emerging of Smart devices, such as smart light, smart switch and smart speaker, I believe smart home technology has a great potential and will play an essential role in our future life. And I want to be a part of it, that is, to build a smart home product that can help people save energy and make our everyday life pleasant and more enjoyable. With this goal in mind, I began to build a smart home prototype to put my vision into real project. After numerous try out and lots of updates, the prototype is ready and its user experience lives beyond my expectation. I believe it is time to have a CTO/Co-founder join me so together we can launch our product to the market and build something great of the home automation market. 

What we have done so far:
Has built and launched a prototype;
iOS app prototype ready;
Extensively tested the prototype;

As CTO/Co-founder Your primary responsibility will be: 
Product Development based on the prototype;
Firmware and PCB development;
Mobile App building and Server deployment;


Compensation:

Equity ONLY (>20%, depending on your contribution). What I am looking for is a tech partner/co-founder, not an employee. 

Potential candidate:
Passionate about iOT and consumer technology;
Eager to learn and embrace challenge;
Desire entrepreneurship and has the ambition to build something valuable in your future life;
Willing to have a serious and long term commitment into this partnership


